However, due to server tick timer its never the case. Even on the best of days keeping 4 contantly up is impossible. More often then not one will drop. Then tack on missed notes, and that dam drop song bug (song hits JUST as the song drops and you get a stop song message, a song landed message, then anothewr stopped song message).<br>
If i was to have designed bards song casting system it would consisted of a song box and you just drag the songs you want into it and they would ALL be pulsed ever 12 seconds.<br>
Mashing keys every 3 seconds is dam annoying and in no way fun. Why should i have to consentrate on the game 100% of the time when classes like warriors, rogues, and most casters can make a nice hotkey to do 10-30seconds worth of commands. This is mostly an issue with missed notes. Its primarly because of that dam annoy &quot;feature&quot; we have to focus so much dam attention to playing songs. Its not like anything we have is so important that it involves so much attention. It would be like adding a random &quot;your spell is about to collapse&quot; on cheal every 3 seconds as its casting and if you didnt press a button right away cheal wouldnt land.<br>
<br>
Sure people say, twisting is the skill that makes a good bard stand out. FUCK that. Twisting makes me fucking sleepy. It makes me bored it MAKES MY FUCKING HAND HURT NIGHT AFTER NIGHT.<br>
<br>
HAHA i guess i went on a bit of a rant there. But hell ive been twisting for over 5 years. I think i have that right :P <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46500" target="top">Pinene</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
