<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Main Point: All casters get AAs to extend their spells and get the benefit of spell haste, how come bards don't too?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There is no good reason why we don't. That should be addressed in the next batch of AAs we see from SOE. What real objections can there be to allowing us this simple courtesy that is extended to all casters BUT NOT bards? This would not overpower bards at all. In a standard experience group, how many additional songs beyond the boring standard four (riz/muse, zek, PoV, Marr) would you want to twist during the battle? Charisma? AC buff? Niv's regen? Even if we could add a song into the standard four it is hardly going to make your group materially stronger or kill faster imho.<br>
<br>
I want SOE to introduce a bard AA (maybe require 300 AAs before you can activate it) that for each level will permit the bard's song to be extended one tick. It could be three to five levels of this. <br>
<br>
If for some reason SOE thinks that extending song duration would be too powerful, then I suggest that they let us extend song duration for at least the following song abilities: Mez, lull, slow, debuff, charm. There is no way that this could be overpowering.<br>
<br>
Well those are my thoughts. <br>
<br>
Note: I can still twist four pretty reliably even after DX9.<br>
<br>
