<br>
All in all, if we use any other games as guidelines, this is the first class to cross over and also the last one ... DAoC made sure that twisting was not possible in the early days, and then any other games I have seen that include the equivalent of a Bard, also do not allow for twisting of any kind, and EQ2 won't either, and neither will it have a Bard anywhere near the design that this version of EQ has, and thus, I believe, it will help ensure that the new games will not be able to survive into the higher realms and levels ... plain and simple. That's not to say that the Bard is not the only, and most important class in this game of EQ1, but it is to say that its role is too important in the actual success of any Guild and upper level work that we do. Without a similar class, no game out there stands a chance to even come close to gaining the high level players that this game has been able to keep and work with.<br>
<br>
All in all, what I think SoE should do, is accept the Bard, as the one design that separates this game from all others, as one of the most inventive class designs, and start working to help define it better instead of killing it. The day that we get so nerf'd that we are not important anymore, or we are just like all the other classes ... this game will be over.<br>
<br>
I guess that imitation is the sincerest form of flattery ... but programmers out there are too afraid of doing something creative and different ... to keep the game ten steps above all the competition ... but some leaders at SoE obviously don't see that, or understand that ... and will work on killing the timing and twisting ... in favor of the 3 bard module that DAoC already has for EQ2 ... how original of SoE!<br>
<br>
Go ahead ... tinker with song duration and kill the game! <p>Moshkiae Soulwriter, the non role playing Bard / Mo'riae Soulwriter - Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astuce999>astuce999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#330000>(6/17/04 2:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19506.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Song Duration</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure if your post was referring to mine specifically or to the others below it, would you care to please specify if getting songs extended across the board is what would &quot;kill the game&quot;, to which I agree, or any type of song extension at all.<br>
